The goods purchased by consumers are produced by firms, another key set of
economic players. This unit introduces you to the study of firm, or producer,
behavior. You will learn how to analyze firms' decisions mathematically using a
production function and calculate their optimal level of production, costs, and
profits. In addition, you will begin to learn how firms interact in a
competitive market in the short-run and the long-run.
